SIMPLE: inclement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inclement
<hw>In*clem"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inclemens</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>clemens</ets>
mild: cf. F. <ets>incl⟦eacute⟧ment</ets>. See
<er>Clement</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not clement; destitute of a mild and kind temper;
void of tenderness; unmerciful; severe; harsh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Physically severe or harsh (generally restricted to
the elements or weather); rough; boisterous; stormy; rigorously cold,
etc.; <as>as, <ex>inclement</ex> weather</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The guard the wretched from the <qex>inclement</qex> sky.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Teach us further by what means to shun⟦br⟧
The <qex>inclement</qex> seasons, rain, ice, hail, and snow!</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inclemently</ent>⟦br⟧
